{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.21",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 21 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:1",
      "text": "As the divisions of waters, so the heart of the king is in the hand of the Lord: whithersoever he will, he shall turn it.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:2",
      "text": "Every way of a man seemeth right to himself: but the Lord weigheth the hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:3",
      "text": "To do mercy and judgment, pleaseth the Lord more than victims.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:4",
      "text": "Haughtiness of the eyes is the enlarging of the heart: the lamp of the wicked is sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:5",
      "text": "The thoughts of the industrious always bring forth abundance: but every sluggard is always in want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:6",
      "text": "He that gathereth treasures by a lying tongue, is vain and foolish, and shall stumble upon the snares of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:7",
      "text": "The robberies of the wicked shall be their downfall, because they would not do judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:8",
      "text": "The perverse way of a man is strange: but as for him that is pure, his work is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:9",
      "text": "It is better to sit in a corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman, and in a common house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:10",
      "text": "The soul of the wicked desireth evil, he will not have pity on his neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:11",
      "text": "When a pestilent man is punished, the little one will be wiser: and if he follow the wise, he will receive knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:12",
      "text": "The just considereth seriously the house of the wicked, that he may withdraw the wicked from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:13",
      "text": "He that stoppeth his ear against the cry of the poor, shall also cry himself, and shall not be heard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:14",
      "text": "A secret present quencheth anger: and a gift in the bosom, the greatest wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:15",
      "text": "It is joy to the just to do judgment: and dread to them that work iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:16",
      "text": "A man that shall wander out of the way of doctrine, shall abide in the company of the giants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:17",
      "text": "He that loveth good cheer, shall be in want: he that loveth wine, and fat things, shall not be rich.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:18",
      "text": "The wicked is delivered up for the just: and the unjust for the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:19",
      "text": "It is better to dwell in a wilderness, than with a quarrelsome and passionate woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:20",
      "text": "There is a treasure to be desired, and oil in the dwelling of the just: and the foolish man shall spend it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:21",
      "text": "He that followeth justice and mercy, shall find life, justice, and glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:22",
      "text": "The wise man hath scaled the city of the strong, and hath cast down the strength of the confidence thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:23",
      "text": "He that keepeth his mouth and his tongue, keepeth his soul from distress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:24",
      "text": "The proud and the arrogant is called ignorant, who in anger worketh pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:25",
      "text": "Desires kill the slothful: for his hands have refused to work at all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:26",
      "text": "He longeth and desireth all the day: but he that is just, will give, and will not cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:27",
      "text": "The sacrifices of the wicked are abominable, because they are offered of wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:28",
      "text": "A lying witness shall perish: an obedient man shall speak of victory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:29",
      "text": "The wicked man impudently hardeneth his face: but he that is righteous, correcteth his way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:30",
      "text": "There is no wisdom, there is no prudence, there is no counsel against the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.21.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:31",
      "text": "The horse is prepared for the day of battle: but the Lord giveth safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
